    "The first group consists of authors who use these tools for literature reviews.",
    "These individuals face the risk of including incorrect studies and drawing inaccurate conclusions, potentially jeopardising the quality of their work and their careers.",
    "To mitigate these risks, it is crucial to use tools that demonstrate high performance and transparency, especially in terms of the datasets used and potential biases.",
